{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"efcf04a7-83b9-4784-b1c9-2a71ec104949","content":"Yes, you'll hit **framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for .NET Core/.NET targets. Two of your three TFMs are affected:\n\n| Target Framework | MSTest v3 Compatible? |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Yes |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ No — upgrade to `net6.0`+ |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ No — upgrade to `net6.0`+ |\n\n**Other migration notes:**\n\n1. **Package consolidation** — MSTest v3 offers a single `MSTest` meta-package replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n2. **Breaking API changes** — some deprecated APIs were removed (e.g., `Assert` overloads, `TestContext` property changes, timeout/cleanup behavior changes). Review your test code after upgrading.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd update your TFMs and packages, e.g.:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net6.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n...\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes to your project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a484173d-c81b-46a6-9428-f4f5d4184a69","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 has some important compatibility changes:\n\n1. **Dropped framework support**: MSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `.NET 5.0` is no longer supported (it's out of support from Microsoft)\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` is no longer supported (also out of support)\n   - `.NET Framework 4.6.2` (`net462`) — I need to check this. MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and later, so `net462` should be fine.\n   \nLooking more closely at the requirements, MSTest v3 needs .NET Framework 4.6.2 or later, and for .NET Core/.NET targets it requires .NET 6.0 or later. This means `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` would both need to be upgraded to at least `net6.0`, while `net462` should remain compatible.\n\nMSTest v3 also consolidates the separate test framework and adapter packages into a single `MSTest` meta-package, though the older individual packages still function. Beyond that, there are several breaking changes to be aware of—some APIs were removed or modified, `TestContext` behavior shifted, timeout defaults changed, and how class and assembly cleanup works was altered.","outputTokens":741,"requestId":"1BD4:166832:A889DB:BE929F:6A03ECD7"},"id":"6bee4d38-8688-4f51-85c3-4e73938adf83","timestamp":"2026-05-13T03:15:51.869Z","parentId":"cfd9fed7-0512-47d0-8e21-630d726e14ef"}
